# Day 6 - Triggers and SOQL

## 1. What is SOQL?

SOQL (Salesforce Object Query Language) is used to retrieve data from Salesforce objects.

SOQL allows developers to:

- Search records
- Retrieve specific fields
- Filter data
- Work with relationships

Example:

Retrieve all students from Student object.

---

## 2. What is an Apex Trigger?

An Apex Trigger is code that executes automatically when events happen on records.

Examples of events:

- Insert
- Update
- Delete

Triggers help automate actions after data changes.

---

## 3. Difference Between Flow and Trigger

| Flow | Trigger |
|-------|----------|
| No-code automation | Code-based automation |
| Simple business processes | Complex logic |
| Easy to build | More flexible |
| Drag and drop | Programming required |

---

## Difference Between Before and After Trigger

| Before Trigger | After Trigger |
|----------------|--------------|
| Executes before saving data | Executes after saving data |
| Used for validation | Used for related actions |
| Faster processing | Access generated record IDs |

---

